installation:

For installation, please review the Makefile in the top level
directory (specifically the PREFIX variable). Then type

make && sudo make install

dependencies:

The toolbox depends on the following libraries:

- libjack
- libsndfile
- liblo
- libltc
- gtkmm-2.4 or gtkmm-3.0
- libxml++-2.6
- liblsl-dev
- libfftw3-dev
- libfftw3-single3
- libfftw3-double3
- libcurl4-openssl-dev


For de-installation, please type

  sudo make uninstall

On debian-based systems, the dependencies may be satisfied by typing:

  sudo apt-get install git g++ make build-essential libsndfile1-dev ruby-dev jackd2 portaudio19-dev default-jre libjack-jackd2-dev dpkg-dev lsb-release software-properties-common wget libxml++2.6-dev liblo-dev libltc-dev libasound2-dev libjack-jackd2-dev libgtkmm-3.0-dev libcairomm-1.0-dev libsndfile1-dev libfftw3-dev libfftw3-single3 libfftw3-double3 libcurl4-openssl-dev libwebkit2gtk-4.0-dev libgtksourceviewmm-3.0-dev imagemagick libmatio-dev texlive-latex-recommended texlive-latex-extra vim-common

To build a debian package of liblsl:

install cmake: 
  sudo apt install cmake

clone repository:
  git clone https://github.com/gisogrimm/labstreaminglayer

compile and package:
  mkdir labstreaminglayer/LSL/liblsl/build/
  cd labstreaminglayer/LSL/liblsl/build/
  cmake ..
  make
  cd ../distros/deb/
  ./pack.sh
  sudo dpkg -i liblsl*.deb

The original source of labstreaminglayer is
https://github.com/sccn/labstreaminglayer
